    "The single storey side/rear extension would, by reason of its height, roof form, excessive depth and position close to the boundaries of the site, be an unneighbourly development and  would provide a \"wall of development\" which would give rise to an uncomfortable overbearing effect and sense of enclosure harmful to the amenity of No. 28 Dunmow Drive, including loss of outlook and light, contrary to Policy 7 of the Havering Local Plan and the Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document.",
